
## Users
Contains all endpoints related to the API for Users.

### - Get User Invitation
```shell
# Replace `token` with your invitation token
# Replace `PUBLIC_KEY` with your public key
# Replace `PRIVATE_KEY` with your private key
curl -X GET -H "Content-Type: application/json" -H "api-version: 1" https://dev-api.causemo.com/app/users/invites/:token -u <PUBLIC_KEY>:<PRIVATE_KEY>
```
```javascript
var appAPI = require('causemo-api-client').appAPI; // get app API
var userAPI = appAPI.user; // get User endpoint 
var token = ....;
var authToken = ....;
return userAPI.getUserInvitation(authToken, token)
  .then(console.log.bind(undefined))
  .catch(console.error.bind(undefined));
```
Fetches the details for a user invitation

* **URL:** `/app/users/invites/:token`
* **METHOD:** GET
* **TYPE:** private

### - Accept User Invitation 
```shell
# Replace `token` with your invitation token
# Replace `PUBLIC_KEY` with your public key
# Replace `PRIVATE_KEY` with your private key
curl -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -H "api-version: 1" -d '{...} https://dev-api.causemo.com/app/users/invites/:token -u <PUBLIC_KEY>:<PRIVATE_KEY>
```
```javascript
var appAPI = require('causemo-api-client').appAPI; // get app API
var userAPI = appAPI.user; // get User endpoint 
var token = ....;
var authToken = ....;
var userObj = {...};
return userAPI.acceptUserInvitation(authToken, token, userObj)
  .then(console.log.bind(undefined))
  .catch(console.error.bind(undefined));
```
Accepts user invitation and creates a new user. It will also check that the user email is currently not associated to another user, if it is, server will ask you to authenticate as that user.

* **URL:** `/app/users/invites/:token`
* **METHOD:** POST
* **TYPE:** private

#### BODY:
Parameter | Required | Description
--------- | ------- | -----------
password | true | User password
firstName | true | User first name
lastName | true | User last name
title | false | User job title


